<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 1:02AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Oldham,
northeastern Deaf Smith and southwestern Potter Counties through 130
AM CDT...
At 102 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Vega, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vega and Wildorado.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
